                                <h2>David Hailey
                                    <br><small>Ph.D., University of New Mexico</small></h2>

                                <p>Dr. Hailey has been at Utah State University since 1994 teaching Web design and digital communication technologies such as eBook publication. In his research, using contemporary American genre theory, he examines methods for evaluating quality of content in complex and complicated information systems (CCISs). In the past, he used these same theories to research, design, and develop online instruction for Sandia National Labs, the colleges of engineering at Utah State University and University of Texas. As an aside, he examines emerging technologies and processes (e.g., migrating eBook technologies into corporate documentation), introducing that research into his classrooms. His research writing appears in a broad spectrum of technical communication and engineering publications, as well as book chapters and monographs.</p>

                                <section>

